---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Halliday helps nonprofits turn disconnected data into smarter decisions. We bring 20+ years of data and analytics experience to nonprofit leadership teams."
>
  <!-- Page header -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-primary-dark)] text-white py-20 lg:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-semibold text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">
          About Halliday
        </p>
        <h1
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6"
          style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
        >
          We help nonprofits make sense of their own data
        </h1>
        <p class="text-white/70 text-xl leading-relaxed">
          Because the problem isn't that you don't have data. It's that nobody's connecting it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-[var(--color-surface)]">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16">

        <!-- Main narrative -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-3 space-y-8" data-animate>
          <div>
            <h2
              class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4"
              style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
            >
              Why we started Halliday
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Every nonprofit we've worked with has the same story: donor records in one system, program data in another, grant deliverables in a third — and no way to see the full picture. Leadership makes decisions based on gut instinct because nobody's connected the dots across their data.
              </p>
              <p>
                We started Halliday because we kept seeing organizations with years of valuable data and no structured way to learn from it. Not because they lacked the will — because they lacked a partner who understood both the data and the mission.
              </p>
              <p>
                That's the gap we fill. We bring 20+ years of data warehousing, business intelligence, and analytics experience to the nonprofit sector — not to sell technology, but to help organizations see what their data is already trying to tell them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2
              class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4"
              style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
            >
              How we think about the work
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                We don't start with tools. We start with your data — what you have, where it lives, and what it can tell you. That's why every engagement begins with an Impact Data Review: a fixed-scope diagnostic that surfaces the patterns and insights already sitting in your existing systems.
              </p>
              <p>
                From there, we help you decide what to do about it. Sometimes the answer is an off-the-shelf tool you didn't know existed. Sometimes it's a change in process. And sometimes it's a purpose-built solution that doesn't exist yet — in which case, we build it.
              </p>
              <p>
                We're technology-agnostic. We'll recommend a $50/month SaaS product if that solves your problem, or scope a custom dashboard if it doesn't. The goal is always the same: help you make better decisions with the data you already have.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h2
              class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4"
              style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
            >
              Built for how nonprofits actually operate
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                We know nonprofits operate with small teams, tight budgets, and high accountability to funders and communities. Our work is designed for that reality — not for some idealized scenario with an IT department and a six-figure software budget.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Principles sidebar -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2" data-animate data-animate-delay="200">
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-background)] rounded-2xl p-8 border border-[var(--color-border)] sticky top-24">
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6"
              style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
            >
              How we work
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-6">
              {[
                {
                  title: 'Listen first',
                  body: 'We learn about your organization, your data, and your goals before we suggest anything. There\'s no standard solution to recommend without that context.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Recommend only what creates leverage',
                  body: 'Not every problem needs a custom solution. We\'ll tell you when a simpler approach works — and when it won\'t.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Build for your team',
                  body: 'The best solution is the one your team will actually use. We design around your real constraints — staff capacity, technical comfort, budget.',
                },
                {
                  title: 'Transfer knowledge, not dependency',
                  body: 'When we\'re done, your team understands the system and can manage it independently. We document everything and train thoroughly.',
                },
              ].map((principle) => (
                <li class="flex gap-4">
                  <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-accent)] flex-shrink-0 mt-2" />
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] text-sm mb-1">{principle.title}</p>
                    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-sm leading-relaxed">{principle.body}</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[var(--color-surface)] border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center" data-animate>
      <h2
        class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4"
        style="font-family: var(--font-heading);"
      >
        Ready to see what your data can tell you?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-8">
        Start with an Impact Data Review — or just book a call and tell us what you're working on.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[var(--color-accent)] hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)] text-white px-7 py-3.5 rounded-full font-semibold transition-colors"
      >
        Book a 30-Minute Intro Call
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
